  "text": "Finally, we assessed the evolutionary rates of the viral sphingolipid biosynthesis genes relative to other EhV genes by computing K a and K s values for orthologous gene pairs between two viral strains, EhV-86 and EhV-163 [CITATION_1] ). The substitution rates of the sphingolipid biosynthesis-related genes were found comparable to those of other EhV genes (Fig. 4) . Overall, our results suggest that a negative selection acted on these viral genes, again supporting that they are fully functional.",
